    Sample client program which can send examples of any FIX message.

    On start up this program will attempt to connect to port number 2000 at the TCP/IP address passed in on the command line. If no address is entered on the command line, it will use this machine's address.

    Once a connection is made, it will establish a FIX session.
    It will send a logon message then attempt to send FIX messages as selected from a displayed menu.

    If the program is started with -Dencrypt on the command line, DES encryption will be used, assuming that the encryption package is installed. If the program is started with -Dencrypt=pgp on the command line, PGP encryption will be used, assuming that the encryption package is installed.

    Important Note: Not all messages are appropriate at all times according to the protocol.
    Especially if you are forcing the sending of administration messages, Catalys may report protocol errors and in certain cases may terminate, which is in accordance with the FIX specification for certain types of serious protocol errors.
